2 HOUSE BILL 1486
1 Article – Labor and Employment
2 9–602.
3 (A–1) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES ONLY TO A COVERED EMPLOYEE WHO:
4 (I) WAS CONCURRENTLY EMPLOYED BY MORE THAN ONE
5 EMPLOYER AT THE TIME OF:
6 1. THE ACCIDENTAL PERSONAL INJURY; OR
7 2. THE LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE OF THE COVERED
8 EMPLOYEE TO THE HAZARDS OF AN OCCUPATIONAL DISEASE; AND
9 (II) AS A RESULT OF THE ACCIDENTAL PERSONAL INJURY OR
10 OCCUPATIONAL DISEASE, IS UNABLE TO WORK AT ANY EMPLOYMENT THE COVERED
11 EMPLOYEE WAS ENGAGED IN AT THE TIME OF THE ACCIDENTAL PERSONAL INJURY
12 OR LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE.
13 (2) THE GROSS WEEKLY WAGES FROM THE EMPLOYMENTS THE
14 COVERED EMPLOYEE WAS ENGAGED IN AT THE TIME OF THE ACCIDENTAL
15 PERSONAL INJURY OR LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE SHALL BE COMBINED FOR
16 PURPOSES OF COMPUTING THE AVERAGE WEEKLY WAGE OF THE COVERED
17 EMPLOYEE.
18 (3) THIS SUBSECTION MAY NOT BE INTERPRETED TO CREATE
19 LIABILITY TO PAY COMPENSATION ON THE PART OF ANOTHER EMPLOYER IN WHOSE
20 EMPLOYMENT THE ACCIDENTAL PERSONAL INJURY OR LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE
21 DID NOT OCCUR.
22 (c) For the purpose of computing the average weekly wage of an individual
23 engaged for fire fighting by the Department of Natural Resources who is a covered employee
24 under § 9–207 of this title, the wages of the covered employee shall be:
25 (1) the greater of:
26 (i) any salary or wages received by the covered employee for fire
27 fighting; or
28 (ii) [any salary or wages earned by the covered employee in other
29 employment at the time of the accidental personal injury or last injurious exposure] IF
30 APPLICABLE, THE AVERAGE WEEKLY WAGE CALCULATED UNDER SUBSECTION (A–1)
31 OF THIS SECTION; or

HOUSE BILL 1486 3
1 (2) if the covered employee did not receive wages for fire fighting or from
2 other employment at the time of the accidental personal injury or last injurious exposure,
3 an amount that allows the minimum compensation or death benefits under this title.
4 [(l) (1) This subsection applies only to a covered employee who:
5 (i) has suffered:
6 1. a serious permanent partial disability under § 9–630 of
7 this subtitle; or
8 2. a permanent total disability under § 9–637 of this subtitle;
9 (ii) was concurrently employed by more than one employer at the
10 time of the accidental personal injury;
11 (iii) worked, on average, 20 hours per week or less in the employment
12 in which the accidental personal injury occurred; and
13 (iv) as a result of the accidental personal injury, is unable to work at
14 any employment the covered employee was engaged in at the time of the accidental
15 personal injury or any similar type of employment.
16 (2) (i) If the covered employee earned weekly wages from another
17 employment that exceeded the weekly wages the covered employee earned from the
18 employment in which the accidental personal injury occurred, the average weekly wage of
19 the covered employee shall be based on the weekly wages the covered employee earned in
20 the other employment.
21 (ii) If the covered employee earned weekly wages from two or more
22 other employments and, for more than one of such employments, the weekly wages earned
23 by the employee exceeded the weekly wages of the covered employee from the employment
24 in which the accidental personal injury occurred, the average weekly wage of the covered
25 employee shall be based on weekly wages of the employment where the employee earned
26 the highest wages.
27 (3) This subsection may not be interpreted as:
28 (i) except as provided in §§ 9–630 and 9–637 of this subtitle,
29 relieving from liability to pay compensation the employer in whose employment the
30 accidental personal injury occurred;
31 (ii) creating any liability to pay compensation on the part of another
32 employer in whose employment the accidental personal injury did not occur; or

4 HOUSE BILL 1486
1 (iii) requiring the weekly wages from the employments the employee
2 was engaged in at the time of the accidental personal injury to be combined for purposes of
3 computing the average weekly wage of the covered employee.]
4 9–630.
5 (b) (1) This subsection applies to the payment of weekly compensation
6 required under subsection (a) of this section if the average weekly wage of a covered
7 employee is computed under [§ 9–602(l)] § 9–602(A–1) of this subtitle.
8 (2) The employer in whose employment the accidental personal injury OR
9 LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE TO THE OCCUPATIONAL DISEASE occurred, or the
10 employer’s insurer, shall pay the covered employee weekly compensation that is based on
11 the weekly wages of the covered employee at the employment in which the covered
12 employee was injured OR LAST EXPOSED.
13 (3) Subject to paragraph (4) of this subsection, any additional weekly
14 compensation resulting from computing the average weekly wage based on weekly wages
15 earned by the covered employee in other employment shall be payable in the first instance
16 by the employer in whose employment the employee was injured OR LAST EXPOSED, or
17 the employer’s insurer.
18 (4) Subject to any right of the Subsequent Injury Fund to be impleaded or
19 any right of the Subsequent Injury Fund to defend in a case involving payment from the
20 Subsequent Injury Fund created under Title 10, Subtitle 2 of this article, as allowable under
21 Subtitle 8 of this title, the Subsequent Injury Fund shall reimburse the employer in whose
22 employment the employee was injured OR LAST EXPOSED, or the employer’s insurer, the
23 amount of additional weekly compensation paid by the employer or insurer under
24 paragraph (3) of this subsection.
25 9–637.
26 (c) (1) This subsection applies to the payment of weekly compensation
27 required under subsection (a) of this section if the average weekly wage of a covered
28 employee is computed under [§ 9–602(l)] § 9–602(A–1) of this subtitle.
29 (2) The employer in whose employment the accidental personal injury OR
30 LAST INJURIOUS EXPOSURE TO THE OCCUPATIONAL DISEASE occurred, or the
31 employer’s insurer, shall pay the covered employee weekly compensation that is based on
32 the weekly wages of the covered employee at the employment in which the covered
33 employee was injured OR LAST EXPOSED.
34 (3) Subject to paragraph (4) of this subsection, any additional weekly
35 compensation resulting from computing the average weekly wage based on weekly wages
36 earned by the covered employee in other employment shall be payable in the first instance

